March 11 (Reuters) - London-listed cybersecurity firm Avast (AVST.L) on Friday joined a growing number of Western companies in suspending operations in Russia and Belarus following Moscow's invasion of Ukraine. Ukraine, Russia and Belarus collectively contributed around 1.5% of Avast's revenue last year. Avast said it would give paying users in Ukraine free extensions on their product licenses. Our Standards: The Thomson Reuters Trust Principles.